individual webhooks\n- Does not modify the object (read-only validation)\n- Returns rejection errors from webhooks immediately\n\n## Generic Webhook Infrastructure\n\n**Webhook Base** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/admission/plugin/webhook/generic/webhook.go):\n- `Webhook` type provides common infrastructure for both mutating and validating webhooks\n- `NewWebhook()` creates generic webhooks with configurable source (config manager) and dispatcher\n- Handles webhook client management, authorization checking, and CEL condition evaluation\n\n## Kubernetes-Specific Configuration\n\n**Plugin Registration** (pkg/kubeapiserver/options/plugins.go):\n- `RegisterAllAdmissionPlugins()` registers all kube-apiserver admission plugins\n- `AllOrderedPlugins` defines execution order: mutating plugins first, then validating plugins\n- Mutating webhooks execute before validating webhooks\n- Admission policies (CEL-based) execute in their own positions\n\n**Server Integration** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/options/admission.go):\n- `AdmissionOptions.ApplyTo()` creates the admission chain and sets it on the server config\n- Initializes all plugin initializers including generic and Kubernetes-specific ones\n- Wraps the chain with metrics decorator via `admissionmetrics.WithStepMetrics()`\n\n## Request Handler Integration\n\nThe admission chain is called at request handling time:\n\n- **Create Handler** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/handlers/create.go):\n  - Calls mutating admission via `mutatingAdmission.Admit(ctx, admissionAttributes, scope)`\n  - Calls validating admission via handlers\n\n- **Update Handler** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/handlers/update.go):\n  - Calls mutating and validating admission for UPDATE operations\n\n- **Patch Handler** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/handlers/patch.go):\n  - Calls mutating and validating admission for PATCH operations\n\n- **Delete Handler** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/handlers/delete.go):\n  - Calls admission for DELETE operations\n\n- **REST Handler** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/handlers/rest.go):\n  - Calls admission for CONNECT operations\n\n- **Field Manager** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/handlers/fieldmanager/admission.go):\n  - `NewManagedFieldsValidatingAdmissionController()` wraps admission to validate managed fields\n\nThe execution order ensures mutating plugins run first to modify the request, followed by validating plugins to verify the final state, with webhook re-invocation support for interdependent webhooks."
